org.dspace.rest

Class Resource

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.dspace.rest.Resource
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    BitstreamResource, CollectionsResource, CommunitiesResource, FilteredCollectionsResource, FilteredItemsResource, HandleResource, HierarchyResource, ItemsResource, MetadataRegistryResource

    public class Resource
extends Object
    Superclass of all resource classes in REST API. It has methods for creating context, write statistics, processsing exceptions, splitting a key of metadata, string representation of action and method for getting the logged in user from the token in request header.
    Author:
    Rostislav Novak (Computing and Information Centre, CTU in Prague)

    • Method Detail

      • createContext

        protected static Context createContext(EPerson person)
                                throws ContextException
        Create context to work with DSpace database. It can create context with or without a logged in user (parameter user is null). Throws WebApplicationException caused by: SQLException if there was a problem with reading from database. Throws AuthorizeException if there was a problem with authorization to read from the database. Throws Exception if there was a problem creating context.
        Parameters:
        person - User which will be logged in context.
        Returns:
        Newly created context with the logged in user unless the specified user was null. If user is null, create the context without a logged in user.
        Throws:
        ContextException - Thrown in case of a problem creating context. Can be caused by SQLException error in creating context or finding the user to log in. Can be caused by AuthorizeException if there was a problem authorizing the found user.

        protected static void processException(String message,
                    Context context)
                                throws javax.ws.rs.WebApplicationException
        Process exception, print message to logger error stream and abort DSpace context.
        Parameters:
        message - Message, which will be printed to error stream.

      • getUser

        protected static EPerson getUser(javax.ws.rs.core.HttpHeaders headers)
        Return EPerson based on stored token in headers under "rest-dspace-token".
        Parameters:
        headers - Only must have "rest-api-token" for successfull return of user.
        Returns:
        Return EPerson logged under token in headers. If token was wrong or header rest-dspace-token was missing, returns null.
